            </div>
        <div class="section" id="section-5">
            <div class="section-title">Detailed Research Methodology</div>
                
                <div class="flow-container">
            <div class="flow-step">
                        <div class="step-number">1</div>
                        <div class="step-content">
            <div class="step-title">Literature Search Strategy</div>
                            <div class="step-details">
                                Systematic search of peer-reviewed publications on UK livestock genetic diversity
                                <div class="step-specs">
                                    <strong>Database:</strong> Web of Science<br>
                                    <strong>Search Terms:</strong> (inbreeding OR diversity OR "effective population size") AND (livestock species) AND (UK locations) AND (genomic/genetic/pedigree)<br>
                                    <strong>Date Range:</strong> All publications through 2025-01-13<br>
                                    <strong>Initial Results:</strong> 3,379 papers â†’ 384 after exclusions â†’ 37 final
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="flow-step">
            <div class="step-number">2</div>
                        <div class="step-content">
            <div class="step-title">Inclusion Criteria Application</div>
                            <div class="step-details">
                                Rigorous screening to identify relevant genetic diversity studies
                                <div class="step-specs">
                                    <strong>Species:</strong> Cattle, sheep, pigs, horses, goats, chickens, ducks, turkeys, geese<br>
                                    <strong>Geographic Scope:</strong> UK and Ireland populations<br>
                                    <strong>Required Metrics:</strong> Ne, inbreeding coefficients, or genetic diversity measures<br>
                                    <strong>Exclusions:</strong> Disease studies, simulation papers, non-target species
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="flow-step">
            <div class="step-number">3</div>
                        <div class="step-content">
            <div class="step-title">RBST Watchlist Cross-Reference</div>
                            <div class="step-details">
                                Compare literature coverage with conservation priority breeds
                                <div class="step-specs">
                                    <strong>Reference:</strong> RBST 2024-2025 watchlist<br>
                                    <strong>Categories:</strong> Priority, At Risk, Other Native Breeds, Feral populations<br>
                                    <strong>Analysis:</strong> Identify breeds with/without genetic diversity data<br>
                                    <strong>Outcome:</strong> Gap analysis for conservation prioritization
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="flow-step">
            <div class="step-number">4</div>
                        <div class="step-content">
            <div class="step-title">Data Extraction & Categorization</div>
                            <div class="step-details">
                                Systematic extraction of genetic diversity metrics from identified papers
                                <div class="step-specs">
                                    <strong>Data Types:</strong> Pedigree, microsatellites (SSR), SNP arrays, whole genome sequencing<br>
                                    <strong>Metrics:</strong> Ne (LD-based, F-based), inbreeding coefficients, heterozygosity<br>
                                    <strong>Temporal Matching:</strong> DNA sampling years matched to census data<br>
                                    <strong>Quality Control:</strong> Values extracted from tables, figures, and text
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="flow-step">
            <div class="step-number">5</div>
                        <div class="step-content">
            <div class="step-title">Census Data Integration</div>
                            <div class="step-details">
                                Incorporate government monitoring data for comparison
                                <div class="step-specs">
                                    <strong>Source:</strong> DEFRA 2023 breed inventory<br>
                                    <strong>Method:</strong> Wright's formula for census-based Ne<br>
                                    <strong>Formula:</strong> <div class="formula medium">Ne = 4N<sub>m</sub>N<sub>f</sub>/(N<sub>m</sub> + N<sub>f</sub>)</div><br>
                                    <strong>Assumptions:</strong> Idealized population, random mating, equal sex ratios
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="flow-step">
            <div class="step-number">6</div>
