                        <div class="step-details">
                            <strong>Major Findings:</strong> Significant gaps in genetic monitoring for UK livestock.
                            
                            <ul>
                                <li><span class="highlight">58% of RBST breeds</span> lack genetic diversity data</li>
                                <li><span class="highlight">Complete absence</span> of turkey, duck, goose studies</li>
                                <li><span class="highlight">Census overestimation</span> may hide conservation needs</li>
                                <li>Limited whole genome sequencing studies</li>
                                <li>Outdated genetic assessments for many breeds</li>
                            </ul>
                            
                            <strong>Impact:</strong> Need for targeted genetic studies and improved conservation prioritization based on molecular data.
                        </div>
                    </div>
